estion 3105. There is a direct connection between the previous knowledge points and questions.\n\n3. Student's Knowledge state:\n节点删除, good; 平衡二叉搜索树, good;\n节点删除, bad; 平衡二叉搜索树, bad;\n\n4. The student gets it wrong, likely because of incorrect mastery.\n", "exercise_id: 3258\nexercise content: 本章测试\nIf more than half of the elements in the sequence are equal to m, then m is called a majority (Note: The definition of the majority in many places is the most frequently occurring element, but anyway)序列中若有一半以上的元素同为m，则称m为众数（注：许多地方众数的定义是出现次数最多的元素，不过无妨）If a sequence has a majority, it must be equal to一个序列如果存在众数，则它一定等于\n'A': 'Minimal element最小元素', 'B': 'Median中位数', 'C': 'Average平均数', 'D': 'The average of the maximum element and the minimum element最大元素和最小元素的平均'\nknowledge concepts: ['中位数', '序列', '众数'], is_correct: right\nExplaination: 1. knowledge concepts: ['节点删除', '二叉搜索树']\n\nThe new exercise contains 节点删除, 二叉搜索树.\n\n2. Similar to question 3105. There is a direct connection between the previous knowledge points and questions.\n\n3. Student's Knowledge state:\n节点删除, bad; 平衡二叉搜索树, bad;\n节点删除, bad; 二叉搜索树, bad;\n\n4. The student gets it wrong, likely because of incorrect mastery.\n"]

